<p>I have radio buttons sets inside containers with class named <code>answers</code> the container may be a <code>span</code> or <code>ol</code> i.e:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;ol class="answers"&gt; &lt;!-- radio buttons set here li per each button --&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;  OR &lt;span class="a-panel answers"&gt;&lt;!-- radio buttons set here --&gt;&lt;/span&gt; </code></pre>  <p>All radio sets per each container have unique attribute <code>name</code> value.</p>  <p>I could not able to get the checked value using the following code:</p>  <pre><code>$(".answers").each(function(){ alert($(this).children("input[type=radio]:checked").val()) }) </code></pre>  <p>It always alert undefined. This is a <a href="http://output.jsbin.com/hubomeleka" rel="nofollow">Jsbin DEMO</a></p>